1
00:01:17,544 --> 00:01:21,242
Terra (Portuguese for land)

2
00:01:27,454 --> 00:01:30,685
Terra (Portuguese for land)

3
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:35,626
This was an age of important
geographic discoveries.

4
00:01:35,895 --> 00:01:38,421
Westerners used their knowledge
in navigation

5
00:01:38,665 --> 00:01:40,326
to sail the world.

6
00:01:41,134 --> 00:01:43,967
With them came opportunities
for cultural contacts.

7
00:01:44,204 --> 00:01:47,196
The navigators also gave name to a

8
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,431
beautiful small island in the Pacific.

9
00:01:51,211 --> 00:01:52,235
During the 14th century,

10
00:01:52,479 --> 00:01:55,141
the Renaissance movement
spread across Western Europe.

11
00:01:55,582 --> 00:01:57,107
The Renaissance emphasized

12
00:01:57,350 --> 00:01:59,114
rational thinking,

13
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:03,021
which nurtured humanism and
the spirit of science,

14
00:02:03,556 --> 00:02:05,320
and changed Europe's perspectives

15
00:02:05,558 --> 00:02:08,152
of life and the cosmos.

16
00:02:08,595 --> 00:02:11,621
During the 15th to the 17th centuries,

17
00:02:11,865 --> 00:02:16,359
the Renaissance also led to the advent of
the age of great navigations.

18
00:02:21,674 --> 00:02:25,338
In 1488,
Portuguese navigator Diaz discovered

19
00:02:25,578 --> 00:02:27,444
Cape Town.

20
00:02:28,848 --> 00:02:32,409
In 1492, Spanish navigator
Columbus discovered

21
00:02:32,652 --> 00:02:34,814
the Americas.

22
00:02:40,460 --> 00:02:44,260
In 1498, Portuguese navigator
da Gama discovered

23
00:02:44,464 --> 00:02:46,694
a new navigational route
in the Indian Ocean.

24
00:02:53,706 --> 00:02:57,438
In 1499,
Italian navigator Vespucci discovered

25
00:02:57,677 --> 00:02:59,270
South America.

26
00:03:02,582 --> 00:03:06,382
In 1519, Portuguese navigator
Magellan sailed around the

27
00:03:06,619 --> 00:03:08,314
southern tip of the Americas,
passing through the Pacific

28
00:03:08,555 --> 00:03:12,048
Ocean and arriving at Luzon
island of the Philippines.

29
00:03:12,325 --> 00:03:13,724
With geographical discoveries

30
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,985
and the opening of new sea routes,

31
00:03:16,229 --> 00:03:18,527
men entered the age of sea powers.

32
00:03:18,832 --> 00:03:21,426
European countries
along the Atlantic Ocean

33
00:03:21,668 --> 00:03:23,602
used their knowledge in navigation

34
00:03:23,837 --> 00:03:25,635
to sail the world.

35
00:03:25,872 --> 00:03:26,236
Attracted by huge profit

36
00:03:26,472 --> 00:03:28,964
from spice trading,

37
00:03:29,275 --> 00:03:31,403
they came to Asia.

38
00:03:52,565 --> 00:03:54,761
During the great navigation
age in the 16th century,

39
00:03:55,001 --> 00:03:57,800
western fleets arrived in Asia.

40
00:04:02,742 --> 00:04:06,144
Trade between the East and
the West became frequent.

41
00:04:06,479 --> 00:04:09,176
Yet the Ming Dynasty during that time

42
00:04:09,415 --> 00:04:12,316
adopted stringent policies
to ban maritime trade.

43
00:04:12,552 --> 00:04:15,351
The Ming administration only
accepted tributes offered by

44
00:04:15,588 --> 00:04:17,352
other countries and refused
trade with other countries.

45
00:04:17,790 --> 00:04:18,655
This emboldened ambitious

46
00:04:18,892 --> 00:04:21,224
seafarers to compete

47
00:04:21,394 --> 00:04:24,227
for huge business profits.

48
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:37,641
First,

49
00:04:37,877 --> 00:04:39,709
Japanese businessmen ventured south

50
00:04:39,946 --> 00:04:42,415
to trade in Formosa.

51
00:04:42,649 --> 00:04:45,346
From their Macao base, Portuguese

52
00:04:45,585 --> 00:04:47,713
traveled northbound
passing through Pescadores.

53
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:49,752
On their way to trade in Japan.

54
00:04:50,523 --> 00:04:51,888
Along the coastal areas in China,

55
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:54,685
smuggling by trader groups

56
00:04:54,928 --> 00:04:56,760
was likewise rampant.

57
00:04:59,465 --> 00:05:00,432
In addition,

58
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:03,329
Spanish merchants based
in the Philippines and

59
00:05:03,569 --> 00:05:05,333
the Dutch East India Company,

60
00:05:05,571 --> 00:05:08,097
which was based in southeast Asia,

61
00:05:08,508 --> 00:05:10,033
started to develop trade relations

62
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,278
with China.

63
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:20,351
In this sea trading network,

64
00:05:20,586 --> 00:05:22,213
the sea routes near Formosa

65
00:05:22,422 --> 00:05:25,084
became indispensable
to the foreign sea merchants.

66
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:26,615
Foreign fleets often times

67
00:05:26,859 --> 00:05:29,226
intercepted and sacked one another

68
00:05:29,429 --> 00:05:31,227
due to commercial interests,

69
00:05:31,397 --> 00:05:33,422
which led to increasing conflicts.

70
00:05:35,268 --> 00:05:36,326
Formosa

71
00:05:36,569 --> 00:05:37,661
during that time remained

72
00:05:37,904 --> 00:05:40,532
an untouched paradise,

73
00:05:40,807 --> 00:05:42,775
a land without ruler.

74
00:05:43,409 --> 00:05:45,844
Formosa was unlike China and Japan,

75
00:05:46,079 --> 00:05:49,242
where autonomous administrations existed.

76
00:05:49,816 --> 00:05:52,251
Neither was Formosa like
Ryukyu and Korea,

77
00:05:52,485 --> 00:05:54,419
which were afforded political

78
00:05:54,654 --> 00:05:56,486
protection by the Ming Empire.

79
00:05:57,824 --> 00:05:59,622
During the early 17th century,

80
00:05:59,859 --> 00:06:02,760
the orient seas bustled with trade.

81
00:06:02,996 --> 00:06:06,330
Western powers, oriental traders,
and Japanese pirates

82
00:06:06,566 --> 00:06:08,056
established strongholds

83
00:06:08,301 --> 00:06:10,269
in Formosa in succession.

84
00:06:10,536 --> 00:06:12,504
The island of Formosa, which was located

85
00:06:12,739 --> 00:06:14,366
at the thoroughfare of the seas
in southeast Asia,

86
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:17,575
thus emerged into the world scene

87
00:06:17,810 --> 00:06:20,711
driven by the tides of history.

88
00:06:22,281 --> 00:06:25,512
After the Portuguese and Spaniards,

89
00:06:25,752 --> 00:06:28,881
the Dutch in 1625 was finally

90
00:06:29,122 --> 00:06:32,285
able to draft a more
comprehensive map of Formosa.

91
00:06:32,525 --> 00:06:36,120
As a result,
Formosa became known to the world.

92
00:06:49,642 --> 00:06:51,406
Established in 1602,

93
00:06:51,644 --> 00:06:54,136
the Dutch East India Company

94
00:06:54,380 --> 00:06:56,439
was a trading monopoly

95
00:06:56,682 --> 00:06:58,616
with diplomatic powers
in the countries of residence.

96
00:06:58,951 --> 00:07:01,079
The company was bestowed

97
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:03,618
the power to rule and military power.

98
00:07:09,896 --> 00:07:13,491
In 1622, after being defeated in Macao

99
00:07:13,733 --> 00:07:15,258
by the Portuguese,

100
00:07:15,468 --> 00:07:17,027
the Dutch fleet arrived at Pescadores.

101
00:07:17,370 --> 00:07:19,805
The Dutch East India Company,

102
00:07:20,039 --> 00:07:22,201
upon recommendation
from Chinese pirate-trader

103
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,536
Li Tan and Hsu Hsin-su,

104
00:07:24,811 --> 00:07:28,714
and with tacit consent from the
Hsiamen military commander

105
00:07:28,948 --> 00:07:31,815
in 1624,
retreated from Pescadores to Formosa.

106
00:07:32,485 --> 00:07:34,647
During then, the Ming Empire

107
00:07:34,887 --> 00:07:37,083
did not have explicit rule over Formosa.

108
00:07:37,356 --> 00:07:40,690
The Dutch company thus again landed in

109
00:07:40,927 --> 00:07:44,022
Tayuan Island, which is
present-day Anping in Tainan,

110
00:07:44,263 --> 00:07:45,822
and began its 38-year

111
00:07:46,065 --> 00:07:48,932
colonization of Formosa.

112
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:05,883
The Dutch were skilled

113
00:08:06,119 --> 00:08:08,611
castle builders.

114
00:08:09,055 --> 00:08:10,523
They recruited many Han workers

115
00:08:10,756 --> 00:08:12,622
from coastal regions of China

116
00:08:12,859 --> 00:08:14,884
to build Fort Zeelandia

117
00:08:21,567 --> 00:08:24,366
and Fort Provintia.

118
00:08:25,638 --> 00:08:28,573
To this day, the two castles
have survived battles

119
00:08:28,808 --> 00:08:31,334
and undergone reconstructions
through the years.

120
00:08:31,577 --> 00:08:33,602
They are the predecessors of
Anping Fort and

121
00:08:33,846 --> 00:08:36,213
the Chihkan Tower of today.

122
00:08:37,283 --> 00:08:38,682
The Dutch used the two castles

123
00:08:38,918 --> 00:08:41,216
as stronghold

124
00:08:41,454 --> 00:08:43,786
to rapidly expand to the north and south

125
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:46,685
to colonize Taiwan.

126
00:09:07,713 --> 00:09:10,478
The Dutch company's rule over Formosa

127
00:09:10,716 --> 00:09:13,845
was gradually reinforced
through military actions.

128
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:16,446
The company created
the Council of Formosa

129
00:09:16,689 --> 00:09:19,181
to rule Taiwan.

130
00:09:19,592 --> 00:09:21,390
Under the Council was Zeelandia City,

131
00:09:21,627 --> 00:09:24,824
the municipal court and local assembly.

132
00:09:25,798 --> 00:09:26,890
The municipal court represented

133
00:09:27,133 --> 00:09:29,693
all city residents,

134
00:09:30,069 --> 00:09:31,468
while the local assembly represented

135
00:09:31,704 --> 00:09:34,969
all the aboriginal tribes.

136
00:09:44,350 --> 00:09:46,341
The Dutch governed the island

137
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,452
focusing on the importance of commerce.

138
00:09:48,754 --> 00:09:50,222
Resistance from the aborigines was met

139
00:09:50,456 --> 00:09:52,584
with harsh retaliation.

140
00:09:52,892 --> 00:09:56,453
They repressed resistance
in Matou and Hsiaolung.

141
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:13,245
During the same time,

142
00:10:13,412 --> 00:10:14,811
Dutch missionaries also

143
00:10:15,047 --> 00:10:17,038
actively engaged in missionary work

144
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:19,183
in southern Formosa.

145
00:10:19,685 --> 00:10:20,880
The missionaries built schools and used

146
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,918
Roman scripts to translate the Bible
and prayers

147
00:10:23,222 --> 00:10:25,691
into the dialect of
the plain-dwelling aborigines.

148
00:10:26,592 --> 00:10:28,060
The use of Roman scripts
later became popular among

149
00:10:28,294 --> 00:10:31,195
the plain-dwelling aborigines.

150
00:10:31,364 --> 00:10:34,197
The scripts were frequently
used to draft contracts with

151
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:37,495
the Han people, the so-called
Hsinkang manuscript.

152
00:11:24,950 --> 00:11:27,544
Due to the Dutch rule of Formosa,

153
00:11:27,787 --> 00:11:30,279
other countries became ill at ease.

154
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:31,490
Two years after the Dutch

155
00:11:31,724 --> 00:11:34,193
occupied the south of Formosa,

156
00:11:36,629 --> 00:11:40,088
the Spanish fleet in May 1626

157
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:42,461
arrived at the sea off Santiago Bay

158
00:11:42,702 --> 00:11:44,693
in northeastern Formosa.

159
00:11:44,937 --> 00:11:46,701
The Spaniards occupied Chilong

160
00:11:46,939 --> 00:11:50,170
and held a ceremony of
occupation on Sheliao Island.

161
00:11:52,812 --> 00:11:54,837
The Spaniards built

162
00:11:55,081 --> 00:11:56,845
Fort San Salvador on the island,

163
00:11:57,083 --> 00:11:58,482
and proclaimed their

164
00:11:58,718 --> 00:12:00,618
symbolic rule of Formosa.

165
00:12:13,632 --> 00:12:16,465
In 1628, the Spaniards built

166
00:12:16,702 --> 00:12:18,397
Fort San Domingo

167
00:12:18,637 --> 00:12:21,038
in present-day Tamsui.

168
00:12:21,474 --> 00:12:22,236
This was the origin of the

169
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:24,740
Hungmaocheng in Tamsui,
or City of the Red-Haired,.

170
00:12:25,378 --> 00:12:27,437
The Spaniards used Fort San Domingo

171
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:29,808
as a relay station in sea navigation,

172
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:31,975
as well as a center for ruling

173
00:12:32,284 --> 00:12:33,979
the plain-dwelling aborigines
and Han people.

174
00:12:34,453 --> 00:12:35,113
At the same time,

175
00:12:35,354 --> 00:12:38,756
the fort served as a fortress
for Spanish colonization.

176
00:12:43,295 --> 00:12:46,265
The Spanish church demanded
tributes from the aborigines,

177
00:12:46,532 --> 00:12:48,967
and later incorporated
present-day Taipei basin

178
00:12:49,201 --> 00:12:51,135
and the northeastern coast

179
00:12:51,370 --> 00:12:54,032
into their jurisdiction.

180
00:12:54,306 --> 00:12:56,934
The Spaniards ruled and spread religion.

181
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:42,247
Due to the war with Muslims

182
00:14:42,448 --> 00:14:45,577
in Luzon, the Spaniards moved

183
00:14:45,818 --> 00:14:48,082
their forces to southern Luzon
in the Philippines

184
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:50,687
and decided to concentrate on ruling Luzon.

185
00:14:51,290 --> 00:14:54,351
The Spaniards in 1638

186
00:14:54,593 --> 00:14:56,254
destroyed Fort San Domingo in Tamsui.

187
00:15:11,210 --> 00:15:14,544
In 1642, the Dutch drove
the Spaniards out of Taiwan

188
00:15:14,780 --> 00:15:15,474
and ended Spain's 16-year

189
00:15:15,714 --> 00:15:19,582
rule of northern Formosa.

190
00:15:44,743 --> 00:15:46,370
Another faction composed

191
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:48,046
mainly of Chinese, a few Japanese,

192
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:51,147
and Portuguese

193
00:15:51,383 --> 00:15:53,317
emerged in the meantime.

194
00:15:53,719 --> 00:15:56,654
This was a group of traders
and pirates that engaged

195
00:15:56,889 --> 00:15:59,153
in maritime smuggling.

196
00:15:59,892 --> 00:16:03,419
Among them, Lin Tao-kan, Lin Feng, Li Tan,

197
00:16:03,662 --> 00:16:05,630
Yen Ssu-chi, and Cheng Chih-lung

198
00:16:05,864 --> 00:16:08,697
used Chiayi and Peikang
as their stronghold.

199
00:16:08,934 --> 00:16:11,266
The scope of their activities

200
00:16:11,437 --> 00:16:13,405
extended to Japan, the Philippines,
and Indonesia.

201
00:16:16,241 --> 00:16:19,108
Among these prominent personalities,

202
00:16:19,345 --> 00:16:20,835
the rise of Cheng Chih-lung

203
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:21,774
had significant impact

204
00:16:22,014 --> 00:16:24,574
on the later developments of Taiwan.

205
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:30,214
Cheng had a son with a Japanese woman

206
00:16:30,456 --> 00:16:32,618
named Tagawa. Their son, Fusung,

207
00:16:32,925 --> 00:16:34,290
was to become Cheng Cheng-kung,

208
00:16:34,526 --> 00:16:37,461
who would change Taiwan's history.

209
00:16:38,330 --> 00:16:39,855
The young Cheng Chih-lung

210
00:16:40,099 --> 00:16:40,861
once worked as an interpreter

211
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:43,728
for Dutch Commander Cornelis Reijersen.

212
00:16:51,377 --> 00:16:52,344
Cheng inherited Li Tan's

213
00:16:52,578 --> 00:16:55,047
power after Li's death.

214
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:57,772
He also pledged allegiance
to the Ming Dynasty,

215
00:16:58,017 --> 00:17:01,783
and thus was later able to
eradicate the other pirates

216
00:17:03,288 --> 00:17:05,780
and become a formidable force

217
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:08,687
on the seas southeast of China.

218
00:17:12,798 --> 00:17:15,529
In 1644, the Ching forces invaded China.

219
00:17:15,768 --> 00:17:18,328
Sensing the demise of the Ming Dynasty,

220
00:17:18,570 --> 00:17:21,631
Cheng traveled north to
surrender to the Ching power.

221
00:17:21,907 --> 00:17:23,875
He was, however, detained.

222
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:26,071
His son Cheng Cheng-kung continued

223
00:17:26,311 --> 00:17:28,541
to use Kinmen and Hsiamen
as bases to fight against

224
00:17:28,781 --> 00:17:31,250
Ching administration
and restore the Ming Dynasty.

225
00:17:40,426 --> 00:17:42,793
On Nov. 30, 1646,

226
00:17:43,028 --> 00:17:45,827
Ching attacked Cheng Chih-lung's
base at Anping.

227
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:47,658
They burned and plundered.

228
00:17:47,966 --> 00:17:49,866
Tagawa, who had been separated
for 13 years

229
00:17:50,102 --> 00:17:52,537
and had recently reunited with her son,

230
00:17:52,771 --> 00:17:55,240
committed suicide to avoid disgrace.

231
00:17:55,741 --> 00:17:57,732
A traumatized Cheng Cheng-kung

232
00:17:57,976 --> 00:17:59,273
decided to burn

233
00:17:59,445 --> 00:18:01,504
his scholar clothes

234
00:18:01,747 --> 00:18:03,738
to pursue a military career,

235
00:18:03,982 --> 00:18:06,417
and show his absolute determination.

236
00:18:39,918 --> 00:18:41,113
In 1659,

237
00:18:41,353 --> 00:18:43,788
after a major defeat in Nanking,

238
00:18:44,022 --> 00:18:45,046
Cheng retreated to Hsiamen

239
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:46,815
to regroup his forces

240
00:18:47,059 --> 00:18:49,926
in preparation for the next offensive.

241
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:36,469
A former interpreter of the

242
00:19:36,708 --> 00:19:39,541
Dutch East India Company,

243
00:19:39,778 --> 00:19:40,939
Ho Pin, absconded to Hsiamen
to evade creditors.

244
00:19:41,246 --> 00:19:43,647
Ho presented a map of
the island of Taiwan,

245
00:19:43,882 --> 00:19:46,647
then called Tayuan Island,

246
00:19:46,885 --> 00:19:49,252
and used the island's abundant resources

247
00:19:49,488 --> 00:19:51,217
to persuade Cheng to invade Tayuan.

248
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:01,458
Agonizing over provisions,

249
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:04,397
Cheng readily accepted Ho's proposal.

250
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:26,346
On April 29, 1661,

251
00:21:26,585 --> 00:21:28,519
Cheng, a talented military strategist,

252
00:21:28,754 --> 00:21:32,281
knew that the Luerhmen waterway
would be too shallow and narrow

253
00:21:32,524 --> 00:21:34,424
for large ships to enter,

254
00:21:34,660 --> 00:21:36,754
and that there were
no Dutch sentries on site.

255
00:21:36,995 --> 00:21:38,827
So despite wind and rain,

256
00:21:39,064 --> 00:21:40,532
he led his fleet

257
00:21:40,766 --> 00:21:42,234
of more than over 300 ships

258
00:21:42,467 --> 00:21:45,198
to rush to Luerhman from Pescadores.

259
00:21:48,507 --> 00:21:51,306
On April 30, 1661 at dawn,

260
00:21:51,543 --> 00:21:53,739
Cheng arrived at Luerhmen.

261
00:21:53,979 --> 00:21:57,040
He ordered his officers

262
00:21:57,282 --> 00:21:58,249
to set up an altar

263
00:21:58,483 --> 00:22:00,349
to pray for divine help.

264
00:22:00,919 --> 00:22:02,978
Cheng chose to use Luerhmen waterway

265
00:22:03,221 --> 00:22:05,087
to launch a surprise offensive
on the inner sea at Taichiang

266
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:07,486
because Luerhmen was vulnerable

267
00:22:07,726 --> 00:22:09,160
against a surprise attack.

268
00:22:09,394 --> 00:22:11,453
The element of surprise could

269
00:22:11,697 --> 00:22:14,632
also help Cheng avoid heavy
fire from Fort Zeelandia and

270
00:22:14,866 --> 00:22:17,096
attack Fort Provintia instead.

271
00:23:11,490 --> 00:23:15,017
After praying,
Cheng had the water depth tested,

272
00:23:15,327 --> 00:23:18,228
and the water had indeed
risen by over three meters.

273
00:23:19,131 --> 00:23:21,623
Cheng knew that it was the
first day of the lunar month

274
00:23:21,867 --> 00:23:23,028
and that the tide would rise,

275
00:23:23,268 --> 00:23:25,760
helping his ships to sail in easily.

276
00:23:26,004 --> 00:23:27,768
Yet, he burned incense and prayed.

277
00:23:28,006 --> 00:23:30,031
His purpose was to lead his soldiers

278
00:23:30,275 --> 00:23:31,765
to believe that there was divine help,

279
00:23:32,010 --> 00:23:33,910
and it raised morale.

280
00:23:38,583 --> 00:23:40,779
German surveyor Philip Meij

281
00:23:41,019 --> 00:23:43,579
had lived in Formosa
for 19 years and worked

282
00:23:43,822 --> 00:23:46,848
for Dutch East India Company.

283
00:23:47,192 --> 00:23:48,626
Through his diary,

284
00:23:48,860 --> 00:23:50,794
we come to understand that

285
00:23:51,029 --> 00:23:54,727
the battle was to
decide Taiwan's destiny.

286
00:23:56,168 --> 00:23:58,660
Last day of April 1661.

287
00:23:58,904 --> 00:24:01,464
About 10 a.m. Saturday.

288
00:24:01,706 --> 00:24:04,471
I was at the Han hospital

289
00:24:04,709 --> 00:24:07,804
outside Provintia instructing masons

290
00:24:08,046 --> 00:24:10,481
working on the front gate.

291
00:24:10,715 --> 00:24:15,118
Suddenly I saw flags floating
on the castle in Tayuan.

292
00:24:15,353 --> 00:24:16,650
I thought

293
00:24:16,888 --> 00:24:20,791
the commander wanted to ferry back.

294
00:24:21,026 --> 00:24:23,620
So, I went to Provintia.

295
00:24:23,862 --> 00:24:26,957
There I heard the news that

296
00:24:27,265 --> 00:24:34,467
hundreds of junk ships
led by Koxinga had arrived

297
00:24:34,706 --> 00:24:38,609
at Luerhmen harbor.

298
00:24:38,844 --> 00:24:41,677
Deputy Governor Jacob Valentyn

299
00:24:41,913 --> 00:24:44,746
hurried back from Tayuan.

300
00:24:44,983 --> 00:24:48,385
So I went to Fort Provintia.

301
00:24:48,620 --> 00:24:50,452
There were many junk ships.

302
00:24:50,689 --> 00:24:52,748
I wasn't able to
count the ships in my haste.

303
00:24:52,991 --> 00:24:56,757
Several ships

304
00:24:56,995 --> 00:25:00,659
have already entered Luerhmen harbor.

305
00:25:00,899 --> 00:25:03,027
I simply couldn't believe

306
00:25:03,301 --> 00:25:05,963
how the ships were able to

307
00:25:06,204 --> 00:25:09,731
pass through those narrow
and shallow waterways.

308
00:25:11,643 --> 00:25:13,475
Koxinga's forces were unchallenged

309
00:25:13,712 --> 00:25:15,908
right before our eyes.

310
00:25:16,148 --> 00:25:20,949
His forces landed beside the
brick kiln in Chaitou Pier,

311
00:25:21,253 --> 00:25:25,850
about 15 minutes or one kilometer

312
00:25:26,391 --> 00:25:27,825
from Provintia.

313
00:25:28,059 --> 00:25:30,494
The enemy was in full battle gear.

314
00:25:30,729 --> 00:25:34,063
From Jan Sou farm beside
Hsin Kang-che Road,

315
00:25:34,299 --> 00:25:36,563
they marched over the hill in high morale

316
00:25:36,801 --> 00:25:40,237
amid the sounds of
military drums and horns.

317
00:25:40,405 --> 00:25:42,237
Their troops had countless

318
00:25:42,474 --> 00:25:44,568
colorful banners.

319
00:25:44,809 --> 00:25:46,903
Their helmets were shiny.

320
00:25:47,145 --> 00:25:48,977
They had broad swords.

321
00:25:49,281 --> 00:25:52,251
They traveled fast along Inding Street,

322
00:25:52,484 --> 00:25:54,612
They passed through Hagena Forest

323
00:25:54,853 --> 00:25:58,915
and arrived at the small forest by the sea.

324
00:25:59,157 --> 00:26:02,593
They camped behind the small
river north of Provintia.

325
00:26:02,827 --> 00:26:05,057
They set up thousands of tents.

326
00:26:05,297 --> 00:26:08,028
It was 1:30 p.m.

327
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:11,497
Cheng quickly secured the

328
00:26:11,736 --> 00:26:15,639
navigation route between Tayuan
and Chihkan.

329
00:26:15,874 --> 00:26:18,366
They quickly prepared for an attack
on the fort.

330
00:26:24,149 --> 00:26:26,675
I start to heard my subordinates

331
00:26:26,918 --> 00:26:29,944
complaint about hunger and thirst.

332
00:26:30,255 --> 00:26:31,620
I went up the fort

333
00:26:31,856 --> 00:26:35,019
to get some food

334
00:26:35,260 --> 00:26:37,228
for them and for myself.

335
00:26:37,395 --> 00:26:41,832
When I got there, oh god!

336
00:26:42,467 --> 00:26:45,767
The cook was complaining even more.

337
00:26:46,004 --> 00:26:47,699
He told me that

338
00:26:47,939 --> 00:26:55,778
the well was dried up.

339
00:27:01,019 --> 00:27:04,284
Deputy Governor Valentyn,

340
00:27:04,522 --> 00:27:07,583
faced with water and food shortage,

341
00:27:07,826 --> 00:27:09,294
finally decided to abandon the fort.

342
00:27:09,527 --> 00:27:11,757
Cheng moved his forces in,

343
00:27:11,997 --> 00:27:13,692
and secured his first victory.

344
00:27:13,932 --> 00:27:14,524
For his next step,

345
00:27:14,766 --> 00:27:17,667
Cheng planned to take down Fort Zeelandia.

346
00:27:17,902 --> 00:27:20,928
He offered acceptance to
surrender to Fort Zeelandia,

347
00:27:21,239 --> 00:27:23,333
and sent his troops to besiege

348
00:27:23,575 --> 00:27:27,512
the fort from the north, the sea,

349
00:27:27,746 --> 00:27:30,977
and Tayuan.

350
00:27:31,249 --> 00:27:33,650
Cheng knew that with the
southwestern wind blowing,

351
00:27:33,885 --> 00:27:35,614
the Dutch fleet could not travel to its

352
00:27:35,854 --> 00:27:37,015
headquarters in Batavia, Indonesia,
to seek help.

353
00:27:37,255 --> 00:27:39,223
So he left a smaller force

354
00:27:39,424 --> 00:27:42,724
to lay long-term siege to the fort,

355
00:27:43,028 --> 00:27:46,225
while sending the mass of his forces
to work on farmlands.

356
00:27:46,431 --> 00:27:49,492
Cheng had planned for an enduring war.

357
00:27:55,507 --> 00:27:56,668
He wrote endless letters to

358
00:27:56,908 --> 00:28:00,469
Tayuan chief Frederic Coyett
to convince him to surrender.

359
00:28:04,516 --> 00:28:06,610
On May 24, 1661,

360
00:28:06,851 --> 00:28:10,082
Cheng ordered a letter written in Dutch

361
00:28:10,322 --> 00:28:13,656
to be delivered by the

362
00:28:13,892 --> 00:28:15,360
captured Dutch
missionary Antonius Hambroek

363
00:28:15,593 --> 00:28:17,288
to Coyett at Fort Utrecht.

364
00:28:22,634 --> 00:28:25,865
Hambroek was supposed to

365
00:28:26,104 --> 00:28:29,972
convince Coyett to surrender,

366
00:28:30,241 --> 00:28:32,471
but instead he convinced Coyett
to battle on until

367
00:28:32,711 --> 00:28:35,646
reinforcement arrived from
the Batavia headquarters.

368
00:28:39,584 --> 00:28:41,643
I am well aware

369
00:28:41,953 --> 00:28:46,914
that saying this means the end for me,

370
00:28:47,792 --> 00:28:53,390
but I cannot discharge my obligations

371
00:28:54,432 --> 00:28:58,767
to God and the company if I cower.

372
00:28:59,637 --> 00:29:00,866
I would rather take a thousand risks,

373
00:29:01,106 --> 00:29:02,835
putting me and my wife in physical danger,

374
00:29:03,074 --> 00:29:04,064
than allow myself to be used by the enemy.

375
00:29:04,309 --> 00:29:05,242
I would not betray God,

376
00:29:05,410 --> 00:29:07,902
and be a traitor to my country.

377
00:29:20,859 --> 00:29:23,920
From Aug. 11 to 12, 1661,

378
00:29:24,229 --> 00:29:26,596
an armada of 10 Dutch ships

379
00:29:26,831 --> 00:29:28,526
and a sail boat

380
00:29:28,767 --> 00:29:30,667
appeared at sea in Tayuan.

381
00:29:31,369 --> 00:29:33,565
Cheng was shocked because

382
00:29:33,805 --> 00:29:35,569
he had sent most of

383
00:29:35,807 --> 00:29:37,741
his troops to cultivate land
in different places,

384
00:29:37,976 --> 00:29:39,967
and it was impossible to recall them.

385
00:29:59,764 --> 00:30:01,892
Fortunately the weather turned bad,

386
00:30:02,133 --> 00:30:04,727
and the Dutch armada took shelter
in Pescadores.

387
00:30:09,307 --> 00:30:14,802
Our hope vanished.

388
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:17,710
There was a strong wind.

389
00:30:17,949 --> 00:30:20,680
The weather was getting worse.

390
00:30:21,286 --> 00:30:23,186
Our ships were forced to leave.

391
00:30:23,354 --> 00:30:24,879
Worse, the next day we heard

392
00:30:25,123 --> 00:30:26,386
that Urck ran aground near Masha Channel.

393
00:30:26,624 --> 00:30:32,495
Everyone onboard was captured
by the enemy.

394
00:30:56,120 --> 00:30:57,019
September

395
00:30:57,255 --> 00:30:59,587
Calm weather enabled

396
00:30:59,824 --> 00:31:03,124
the Dutch armada to enter Zeelandia.

397
00:31:19,244 --> 00:31:20,302
But Cheng used

398
00:31:20,545 --> 00:31:22,809
his many lighter,

399
00:31:23,047 --> 00:31:24,811
shallow-water ships

400
00:31:25,049 --> 00:31:26,915
to again win the battle.

401
00:31:51,543 --> 00:31:53,671
In the sea battle in Taikang on Sept. 16,

402
00:31:53,912 --> 00:31:54,811
Cheng's strategy

403
00:31:55,046 --> 00:31:58,812
was to fire cannons from land and sea

404
00:31:59,050 --> 00:32:01,781
and send sail boats and gun ships

405
00:32:02,020 --> 00:32:04,045
to surround and attack the Dutch fleet.

406
00:32:39,891 --> 00:32:41,450
In the heat of the battle,

407
00:32:41,693 --> 00:32:43,252
the Dutch's Kou Keren

408
00:32:43,428 --> 00:32:46,261
was destroyed by Cheng's cannons.

409
00:32:46,497 --> 00:32:48,465
Another vessel ran aground

410
00:32:48,700 --> 00:32:50,134
and was destroyed

411
00:32:50,368 --> 00:32:52,996
by a Chinese gun ship.

412
00:33:07,318 --> 00:33:09,446
After the crushing defeat on
the inner sea at Taichiang,

413
00:33:09,687 --> 00:33:12,281
Coyett and the Council of Formosa decided

414
00:33:12,457 --> 00:33:14,892
to play the defensive.

415
00:33:18,262 --> 00:33:21,926
Jan. 17, 1662

416
00:33:22,166 --> 00:33:25,830
Those who had defected urged Koxinga

417
00:33:26,070 --> 00:33:29,472
not to attack Fort Zeelandia,

418
00:33:29,707 --> 00:33:34,338
but the people inside the
fort wanted Cheng to attack.

419
00:33:34,579 --> 00:33:40,541
The defectors urged Cheng
to attack Fort Utrecht,

420
00:33:40,785 --> 00:33:44,585
which was worth attacking.

421
00:33:45,089 --> 00:33:49,083
The next target would be the
redoubt located at the beach,

422
00:33:49,327 --> 00:33:52,729
which would be easy to take down.

423
00:33:52,964 --> 00:33:57,595
Then, without losing many soldiers,

424
00:33:57,835 --> 00:34:01,999
it would be easy to capture the forte.

425
00:34:02,306 --> 00:34:05,332
And enter the city.

426
00:34:05,743 --> 00:34:08,007
Within a short time,

427
00:34:08,312 --> 00:34:12,271
it would be possible to place mines
below the official residence

428
00:34:12,517 --> 00:34:15,145
in Amsterdam Bastion,

429
00:34:15,386 --> 00:34:16,547
and blow up the entire place.

430
00:34:16,788 --> 00:34:18,847
Jan. 25, 1662,

431
00:34:19,090 --> 00:34:21,889
A cannon battle unprecedented

432
00:34:22,126 --> 00:34:25,027
in Taiwan's history began in
the former Tayuan Island.

433
00:34:25,263 --> 00:34:28,233
Cheng's troops attacked Fort Utrecht

434
00:34:28,399 --> 00:34:29,662
with 30 big cannons.

435
00:34:29,901 --> 00:34:31,801
In the simultaneous attack
on Fort Zeelandia

436
00:34:32,036 --> 00:34:34,232
and Fort Utrecht,

437
00:34:34,439 --> 00:34:36,430
Cheng's army fired 2500

438
00:34:36,674 --> 00:34:38,574
cannon shots in one day.

439
00:34:38,810 --> 00:34:40,676
They destroyed Fort Utrecht,

440
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:41,845
and totally smashed

441
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:44,572
the Dutch's will to fight.

442
00:36:00,858 --> 00:36:03,259
Jan. 30, 1662

443
00:36:03,494 --> 00:36:06,828
Under siege for 275 days,

444
00:36:07,064 --> 00:36:08,554
Fort Zeelandia finally opened its gates,

445
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:11,030
and the Dutch relinquished their rule.

446
00:36:11,302 --> 00:36:12,269
This was the first transfer of power

447
00:36:12,436 --> 00:36:14,905
in Taiwan's history.

448
00:36:29,587 --> 00:36:33,217
You have been under siege
for nine months.

449
00:36:33,424 --> 00:36:34,391
The fault

450
00:36:34,625 --> 00:36:36,525
is all yours.

451
00:36:36,761 --> 00:36:38,525
What else can you say?

452
00:36:38,763 --> 00:36:41,255
Do you think I am satisfied

453
00:36:41,499 --> 00:36:43,092
to have taken the fort?

454
00:36:43,334 --> 00:36:45,598
All you people who think you're smart

455
00:36:45,837 --> 00:36:48,238
can think about this.

456
00:37:10,061 --> 00:37:12,257
We agree to
surrender Castle Zeelandia and

457
00:37:12,496 --> 00:37:18,629
other properties belonging to
the Company to Lord Koxinga,

458
00:37:18,870 --> 00:37:21,669
except for the company's books,
documents,

459
00:37:21,906 --> 00:37:24,307
and servants.

460
00:37:24,575 --> 00:37:25,838
Also, we want to load
and ship all articles needed

461
00:37:26,077 --> 00:37:28,273
by our personnel during

462
00:37:28,512 --> 00:37:33,609
their voyage to Batavia.

463
00:37:46,564 --> 00:37:48,623
We fully agree

464
00:37:48,866 --> 00:37:51,858
with your practice of

465
00:37:52,103 --> 00:37:55,733
letting your soldiers board the ships

466
00:37:55,973 --> 00:37:57,304
with flying banners, burning fusees,

467
00:37:57,541 --> 00:37:59,566
and loaded rifles.

468
00:38:06,284 --> 00:38:08,514
For your voyage to Batavia,

469
00:38:08,753 --> 00:38:11,950
1 allow you to take the food, water,

470
00:38:12,189 --> 00:38:13,350
and ammunitions

471
00:38:13,591 --> 00:38:17,528
you will need.

472
00:38:43,321 --> 00:38:46,518
I was released and ordered

473
00:38:46,757 --> 00:38:49,055
to go with their hostages

474
00:38:49,293 --> 00:38:50,954
to Fort Zeelandia.

475
00:38:51,262 --> 00:38:53,390
Among 300 people only three survived.

476
00:38:53,631 --> 00:38:55,224
One of them finally

477
00:38:55,433 --> 00:38:58,801
returned to their friends,

478
00:38:59,036 --> 00:39:01,004
back to Christians

479
00:39:01,272 --> 00:39:04,037
Praise and thanks to God the almighty.

480
00:39:04,275 --> 00:39:08,803
God protected me

481
00:39:09,046 --> 00:39:12,243
in times of difficulty and danger.

482
00:39:12,483 --> 00:39:16,647
God let me regain freedom.

483
00:39:23,894 --> 00:39:26,226
Feb. 9, 1662

484
00:39:26,464 --> 00:39:28,091
Women and children

485
00:39:28,332 --> 00:39:30,061
living in aboriginal villages

486
00:39:30,301 --> 00:39:32,633
returned to Fort Zeelandia.

487
00:39:32,870 --> 00:39:34,736
Led by Tayuan governor Coyett,

488
00:39:34,972 --> 00:39:36,997
over 900 soldiers
in full battle gear marched

489
00:39:37,241 --> 00:39:40,006
out of Fort Zeelandia.

490
00:39:40,277 --> 00:39:41,870
Some 2000 Dutch soldiers and civilians

491
00:39:42,113 --> 00:39:44,514
boarded eight Dutch ships

492
00:39:44,749 --> 00:39:46,308
waiting to set sail.

493
00:39:48,853 --> 00:39:49,843
Coyett surrendered the key to

494
00:39:50,087 --> 00:39:52,522
Fort Zeelandia at the beach.

495
00:39:52,757 --> 00:39:54,987
Cheng led his soldiers

496
00:39:55,259 --> 00:39:57,887
and entered Fort Zeelandia

497
00:39:58,129 --> 00:40:00,063
through the ruined Fort Utrecht.

498
00:40:00,297 --> 00:40:02,925
Cheng thus took over the
Dutch East India Company.

499
00:40:03,167 --> 00:40:04,396
This was the first transfer of power

500
00:40:04,635 --> 00:40:07,730
in Taiwan's history.

501
00:40:10,741 --> 00:40:13,108
Feb. 17, 1662

502
00:40:13,344 --> 00:40:15,574
The last Tayuan governor Coyett

503
00:40:15,813 --> 00:40:19,408
led the Dutch army and civilians on their

504
00:40:19,650 --> 00:40:22,176
return trip to Batavia;

505
00:40:22,420 --> 00:40:23,751
thus, ending 38 years of colonial rule

506
00:40:23,988 --> 00:40:27,049
of Formosa island by the Dutch.

507
00:40:51,315 --> 00:40:53,977
On June 23, 1662

508
00:40:54,251 --> 00:40:55,741
The hero Cheng,

509
00:40:55,986 --> 00:40:58,216
shortly after taking over Fort Zeelandia,

510
00:40:58,389 --> 00:41:00,221
suddenly passed away.

511
00:41:00,458 --> 00:41:02,825
He was 39.

512
00:41:14,572 --> 00:41:18,031
Cheng was succeeded
by his son Cheng Ching,

513
00:41:18,275 --> 00:41:20,972
who changed the island's name
to Kingdom of Tungning.

514
00:41:37,428 --> 00:41:39,692
Because Cheng Cheng-kung
stationed the military on farmlands,

515
00:41:39,930 --> 00:41:42,456
the relations
with the aborigines is tense.

516
00:41:42,733 --> 00:41:44,223
During Cheng Ching's time,

517
00:41:44,468 --> 00:41:48,029
Han villages began to emerge rapidly;

518
00:41:48,272 --> 00:41:50,639
conflicts with aboriginals worsened.

519
00:41:50,875 --> 00:41:54,106
Troops were sent
to subdue the aboriginal tribes.

520
00:41:54,512 --> 00:41:56,776
There were at least seven large-scale

521
00:41:57,014 --> 00:41:58,846
military actions on record.

522
00:42:18,702 --> 00:42:19,567
To totally eliminate

523
00:42:19,803 --> 00:42:21,669
the influence of Christianity,

524
00:42:21,906 --> 00:42:24,238
churches were turned into temples.

525
00:42:24,909 --> 00:42:27,708
The Confucius Temple
was completed in 1666.

526
00:42:27,945 --> 00:42:30,312
Existing schools were changed
to Han schools.

527
00:42:30,814 --> 00:42:32,441
Aborigines who used Roman scripts

528
00:42:32,683 --> 00:42:34,549
and practiced the Christian faith

529
00:42:34,785 --> 00:42:37,254
had to relearn Han culture.

530
00:42:44,461 --> 00:42:47,522
In 1651, Cheng's general
Shih Lang betrayed Cheng

531
00:42:47,765 --> 00:42:49,324
and surrendered to
the Ching Dynasty due to his

532
00:42:49,567 --> 00:42:51,626
resentment against Cheng Cheng-kung.

533
00:42:51,936 --> 00:42:55,031
Cheng Cheng-kung had put
Shih's father to the sword.

534
00:42:55,306 --> 00:42:57,274
To avenge his father,

535
00:42:57,474 --> 00:42:59,169
Shih continued to write and urge

536
00:42:59,410 --> 00:43:02,277
the Ching Emperor to attack Taiwan.

537
00:43:14,325 --> 00:43:16,020
In June 1683,

538
00:43:16,260 --> 00:43:19,423
the Ching administration accepted
Shih's proposal to attack Taiwan.

539
00:43:32,843 --> 00:43:36,302
Shih led 200 ships to
invade Pescadores.

540
00:43:36,880 --> 00:43:40,248
Cheng Ko-shuang, son of Cheng Ching,
surrendered to the Ching Emperor,

541
00:43:40,718 --> 00:43:42,652
thus ending the “Cheng dynasty”

542
00:43:42,886 --> 00:43:46,254
that had dominated the seas
for half a century.

543
00:43:46,957 --> 00:43:49,358
On Dec. 22, 1683

544
00:43:49,593 --> 00:43:51,721
Shih wrote the Ching Emperor

545
00:43:51,962 --> 00:43:54,863
strongly opposing the
decision to abandon Taiwan.

546
00:43:56,433 --> 00:43:59,459
In 1684, the Ching Dynasty

547
00:43:59,703 --> 00:44:02,263
incorporated Taiwan into its domain.

548
00:44:11,115 --> 00:44:12,913
Since the late 17th century,

549
00:44:13,150 --> 00:44:15,380
the Han Chinese's notion of
“Taiwan island”

550
00:44:15,619 --> 00:44:17,348
gradually extended from Anping in Tainan

551
00:44:17,588 --> 00:44:19,420
to Tainan County and City,

552
00:44:19,657 --> 00:44:22,217
and lastly, to the entire island.

553
00:44:29,333 --> 00:44:31,358
During the early days of its rule,

554
00:44:31,602 --> 00:44:32,865
the Ching administration adopted

555
00:44:33,103 --> 00:44:35,231
an attitude toward Taiwan,
this small island overseas,

556
00:44:35,439 --> 00:44:38,568
that was different
from its rule of the mainland

557
00:44:38,876 --> 00:44:40,776
To prevent immigrants
from causing trouble,

558
00:44:41,011 --> 00:44:43,275
it issued proclamations to restrict

559
00:44:43,514 --> 00:44:44,504
coastal residents in Fuchien
and Kuangtung

560
00:44:44,748 --> 00:44:47,240
from illegally immigrating to Taiwan.

561
00:44:47,418 --> 00:44:47,850
Yet

562
00:44:48,085 --> 00:44:51,282
the waves of immigrants
could not be halted.

563
00:44:55,292 --> 00:44:57,556
Han immigrants continued

564
00:44:57,795 --> 00:45:01,060
to risk their lives to cross
the Black Water Ditch to

565
00:45:01,298 --> 00:45:03,392
come to the island paradise

566
00:45:03,634 --> 00:45:06,035
of Taiwan

567
00:45:06,303 --> 00:45:08,101
in search for better lives.

568
00:45:24,521 --> 00:45:26,512
Formosa, once rich in oceanic culture

569
00:45:26,757 --> 00:45:29,317
and international flavors,

570
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:32,825
became quickly immersed
in mainland culture.

571
00:45:33,063 --> 00:45:35,225
It was the beginning of the 300-year

572
00:45:35,399 --> 00:45:38,027
Han Chinese culture era in Taiwan.

